        "notes": "Supports `new FinalizationRegistry(cleanupCallback)` in construct positions plus `register(target, heldValue, [unregisterToken])`, `unregister(token)`, and `%Symbol.toStringTag%`. Cleanup callbacks are queued through a host-managed finalization queue and become deterministic in tests when a host-opt-in non-standard global `gc()` helper forces collection. js2il does not yet expose a full first-class `FinalizationRegistry` constructor/prototype object on `globalThis`, and cleanup timing otherwise depends on .NET GC plus event-loop checkpoints."
